{
  "texts": [
    "• In the dimension of Learning Methods, the learning process for communication typically requires instantaneous feedback from agents who receive and act upon messages.",
    "This feedback could be in the form of gradient information or changes in the policies or rewards of the receiving agents.",
    "However, obtaining instantaneous feedback from other agents might not always be feasible in real-time decision-making systems.",
    "Despite this challenge, agents can still observe changes in the environment and their rewards to self-evaluate the effectiveness of their communication.",
    "This self-evaluation process enables agents to update and learn their communication protocols over time."
  ]
}